				<h3>
	This page is updated frequently to provide parents and educators with information and resources during the on-site closure of Arkansas public schools.</h3>
<div>
	The closure of on-site instruction for K-12 schools has been extended to the end of the 2019-2020 school year. Education will continue through alternative methods of instruction (AMI). Arkansas AMI, the partnership between the Division of Elementary and Secondary Education (DESE) and Arkansas PBS television, has been expanded through May 22.</div>
<div>
	 </div>
<div>
	Districts will continue development of AMI content so that instruction of students can continue at home. Read <strong><a href="https://governor.arkansas.gov/news-media/press-releases/governor-hutchinson-announces-all-schools-to-remain-closed-for-remainder-of">Gov. Asa Hutchinson's press release</a> </strong>and the<strong> <a href="http://adecm.arkansas.gov/Attachments/AMI_Instructional_Guidance_085903.pdf">Arkansas Instructional Guidance for Extended Year AMI</a>.</strong>
</div>
<div>
